1
00:00:01,220 --> 00:00:04,980
Episode 24

2
00:00:04,980 --> 00:00:07,050
Grandma.

3
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:10,080
Please eat this on your way back.

4
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,720
You didn't have to do that.

5
00:00:20,690 --> 00:00:27,290
When Ju Wan first said he wanted to play cello

6
00:00:27,290 --> 00:00:30,790
he was nine years old, I think?

7
00:00:30,790 --> 00:00:34,120
He asked me buy him a cello,

8
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:38,780
so he begged for a whole month, having a temper tantrum in front of me.

9
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:45,970
So I told him that if he didn't  miss one day of cleaning work for a year, I would buy it for him.

10
00:00:45,970 --> 00:00:48,380
He did it.

11
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:53,670
And then you bought it for him?

12
00:00:54,610 --> 00:00:59,000
The cheapest one, a used one.

13
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,890
And in the end, he used that to win an award.

14
00:01:05,610 --> 00:01:08,930
Since he was young, all his life he had to struggle

15
00:01:08,930 --> 00:01:11,990
to achieve anything.

16
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:17,270
I was sad to see it.

17
00:01:17,270 --> 00:01:25,410
He was born with a lot of talent, but I couldn't support his ambition.

18
00:01:25,410 --> 00:01:28,320
You don't have to think about such things any more.

19
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:30,970
He has the post of permanent Conductor in the Sinyeong Philharmonic.

20
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:41,100
Ju Wan, this boy ... there's something going on with him right now.

21
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:43,870
I can tell with just one look.

22
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:47,130
But this boy, he won't speak.

23
00:01:47,130 --> 00:01:52,360
I know so well that it's useless to try and speak to him about it.

24
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:56,910
Look here, go-fer, let me make a request of you.

25
00:01:56,910 --> 00:02:02,080
If Ju Wan looks like he's having a hard time, ask him what is going on,

26
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:05,310
why he's like that. Please ask him.

27
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,730
I will do that, please don't worry.

28
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,640
Thanks.

29
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:12,080
Did Grandma go home safely?

30
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:16,110
Yes. She said she will contact you when she arrives.

31
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:21,040
I heard that rehearsal was canceled.

32
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:25,220
Yeah, it's a bit chaotic today. Police are coming in and out, too.

33
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:37,780
Can you please leave? I have something to talk about with Conductor.

34
00:03:43,570 --> 00:03:46,350
You should go home for today. We don't even have rehearsal.

35
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:47,970
Yes.

36
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,070
What is it?

37
00:03:57,070 --> 00:04:02,830
The person who died today, he didn't just slip, did he? He was murdered, wasn't he?

38
00:04:02,830 --> 00:04:07,910
Why did that person die here suddenly, on the day of your debut, of all days?

39
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:11,970
How would I know that? That's for the police to know about.

40
00:04:11,970 --> 00:04:15,760
Don't say ...  It's not your doing, right?

41
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,810
Do you really think that I am a murderer

42
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:21,870
or are you thinking that you wish I was one?

43
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:24,090
What is your purpose for asking such a question?

44
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:27,090
I told you, I want to know the truth.

45
00:04:27,780 --> 00:04:30,060
I've been thinking for the last few days

46
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:32,970
about how my relationship with you had no problems before,

47
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:35,690
but how things have become so twisted.

48
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:41,160
Why did this girl Hong Yi Yeong suddenly appear in my life?

49
00:04:41,850 --> 00:04:45,150
And there was only one answer.

50
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:47,430
What is it?

51
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:52,840
I wondered if Hong Yi Yeong was a witness at the incident in which Kim Ian died.

52
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:56,930
Maybe if her memories return, things will become difficult for you?

53
00:04:56,930 --> 00:05:01,480
So maybe you are staying by her side out of desperation?

54
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,630
I enjoyed your novel.

55
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:09,440
I understand why you are doing this.

56
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:12,730
If you're asking me if I'm a murderer, my answer is no.

57
00:05:12,730 --> 00:05:16,880
If you're asking me about my feelings for Yi Yeong, the answer is yes.

58
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,680
So your feelings for her are sincere?

59
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,020
You, Conductor?

60
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:26,190
Please say something that makes sense.

61
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:30,590
Why doesn't it make sense? Am I not capable of sincere feelings?

62
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,700
If you're finished, please go.

63
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:39,540
And work hard towards your goals. Your dream is to become a soloist, isn't it?

64
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:14,410
What are you doing? How can you go there?

65
00:06:14,410 --> 00:06:17,050
I just can't stay still.

66
00:06:17,050 --> 00:06:20,660
Please just stay still, two people have died.

67
00:06:20,660 --> 00:06:24,300
But what if he died because of the item that I found for him?

68
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,420
No, it's not because of that.

69
00:06:25,420 --> 00:06:29,800
But what if it is? If someone died because of me...

70
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:34,350
Yi Yeong, think straight, it's not because of you.

71
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:39,630
Listen to me carefully. You've never met Yun Yeong Gil alone.

72
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:41,580
If anyone comes to ask you about it,

73
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:45,180
just say that he is someone who worked part-time at your Uncle's shop.

74
00:06:46,110 --> 00:06:48,490
I am bad at lying.

75
00:06:48,490 --> 00:06:51,090
They will find out, and I might tell them anyway.

76
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:54,380
He did not die because of Yi Yeong.

77
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:57,780
He asked people for money. He did it to me, too.

78
00:06:57,780 --> 00:07:01,110
I'm sure he asked others as well.

79
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:04,530
What others?

80
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:07,110
Can you think of anyone?

81
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:19,690
Yun Yeong Gil said someone who was a "higher up."

82
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:22,860
It's something the higher-ups want to find at any cost.

83
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:25,050
They are even killing people for it.

84
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:29,770
Now that that person had found the item they were looking for, they no longer needed Yun Yeong Gil who was a headache.

85
00:07:29,770 --> 00:07:33,290
Or maybe Yun Yeong Gil blackmailed them for more money.

86
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:37,420
The answer is close by, so why can't you find it and are asking someone like me?

87
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:40,810
He said the answer is close by.

88
00:07:40,810 --> 00:07:42,270
Close by?

89
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,890
Yes.

90
00:07:45,990 --> 00:07:49,640
In the end, the person who killed Ian also killed Yun Yeong Gil.

91
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:52,860
They both died after they were in possession of the item.

92
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:55,830
Who knows what is in that thing?

93
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:03,980
Is there anything aboutYun Yeong Gil that sticks out in your mind?

94
00:08:03,980 --> 00:08:06,150
Something that sticks out?

95
00:08:06,150 --> 00:08:12,230
The feeling I got when I met him, it seemed like he just needed money.

96
00:08:12,230 --> 00:08:17,480
He acted as if he would give me what he had, as long as I gave him money.

97
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:22,590
He did seem to also want to tell me what happened that day.

98
00:08:22,590 --> 00:08:26,760
So I was wonder if that was his attitude towards you.

99
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:32,120
Thinking about it, he had me listen to a song.

100
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,930
A song?

101
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:47,330
♫ When are you gonna come down? ♫

102
00:08:47,330 --> 00:08:48,640
♫ When are you going to land? ♫

103
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:51,030
It's a song my mother listened to often.

104
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:54,960
He said his mother listened to it often. A gift ...

105
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:56,480
He talked about a gift.

106
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:59,020
A gift? What kind of gift?

107
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:04,630
Don't worry.Even I will want to do something good before I die.

108
00:09:04,630 --> 00:09:07,460
If I happen to die, look for it.

109
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:11,220
I may have left behind a gift for you.

110
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:13,680
He just said "gift."

111
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:17,720
That he could have left me a gift if he died.

112
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:21,630
That I should look for it, and to not forget.

113
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:26,410
Maybe he left something somewhere?

114
00:09:26,410 --> 00:09:31,580
Maybe at your uncle's house or the flower shop? Somewhere he went frequently?

115
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:36,250
I will look for it.

116
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:37,820
Yes.

117
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:43,040
And don't come home, stay at your uncle's. And don't wander around outside.

118
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,490
Alright.

119
00:09:44,490 --> 00:09:46,450
And if a detective comes to question you...

120
00:09:46,450 --> 00:09:48,630
I will tell them I don't know.

121
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:53,420
I'm sorry for getting angry with you this morning.

122
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:58,640
It's not that I don't know how you were feeling when you gave him that item.

123
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,500
No, I was a fool.

124
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,760
No, it's all my fault. I pretended not to know.

125
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:07,620
I never imagined that someone would die.

126
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:10,340
That did not occur to me.

127
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:13,620
Of course, it would have been strange to have thought of that.

128
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:21,500
And don't worry about me. I will do what you ask.

129
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:35,310
After seeing the news, my heart was jumping wildly, and my vision went dark,

130
00:10:35,310 --> 00:10:38,000
and I couldn't think of anything at all.

131
00:10:39,380 --> 00:10:44,180
The Mr. Yun who died at your orchestra building,

132
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:47,490
he is that man who worked at our flower shop, isn't he?

133
00:10:49,370 --> 00:10:51,180
Yes.

134
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:56,380
What in the world... ?

135
00:10:57,090 --> 00:11:03,170
He may have been involved with your incident, and we hired him to work at our shop?

136
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:11,180
And what was he thinking when he came to work at our shop?

137
00:11:11,180 --> 00:11:13,800
Did he do anything to you?

138
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,480
Did he threaten you or something?

139
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:19,010
No, he didn't do anything. Don't worry.

140
00:11:19,010 --> 00:11:21,330
How can I not worry?

141
00:11:21,330 --> 00:11:23,950
He is someone who killed the person you were with by hit-and-run.

142
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:28,390
And that person came to our shop to work, then he died.

143
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,330
You must immediately submit your resignation at work.

144
00:11:34,330 --> 00:11:39,820
Quit timpani and move out of your home. Auntie will take care of everything.

145
00:11:39,820 --> 00:11:45,770
Let's please just forget about this incident.

146
00:11:47,970 --> 00:11:49,370
I can't do that, Auntie.

147
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:55,570
Why can't you?  Is this an ordinary thing? A person has died.

148
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:57,360
I know.

149
00:11:58,530 --> 00:12:02,350
That is all the more reason I can't forget or run away.

150
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:13,220
What will I do with you?

151
00:12:26,970 --> 00:12:30,350
Sorry, I was having a meal and I am late.

152
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:32,800
Did the discussion regarding the album go well?

153
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:35,600
Yes, the chief of staff gave me all the details.

154
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:39,610
So what is your question for me?

155
00:12:39,610 --> 00:12:43,510
In other areas, I am a complete layman.

156
00:12:43,510 --> 00:12:47,850
I am curious why you are looking after me like this.

157
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:52,940
Haven't I told you before? I enjoy your playing.

158
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:57,720
And you asked me to tell you about Professor Kang Myeong Seok.

159
00:12:57,720 --> 00:13:00,230
Yes, I did.

160
00:13:00,230 --> 00:13:04,960
I thought about that, but I don't know much about Professor Kang.

161
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:09,870
Professor Kang operating a secret school, and corruption in college admissions.

162
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,790
That's about it.

163
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:14,390
But those are quite big things, aren't they?

164
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:18,260
But those things can be revealed with just a little digging.

165
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:22,420
I don't think that is all that you came to Sinyeong Philharmonic for.

166
00:13:23,810 --> 00:13:27,130
So please answer me now.

167
00:13:27,130 --> 00:13:30,100
What is your true reason for coming to Sinyeong Philharmonic?

168
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:35,170
Kim Ian who died a year ago, he was your son that you were separated from since he was young, right?

169
00:13:35,170 --> 00:13:39,300
Is it related to that incident?

170
00:13:45,130 --> 00:13:50,140
Do you know how my son died?

171
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:55,930
His entire body was crushed. That was how he died.

172
00:13:55,930 --> 00:13:59,100
He also had a stab wound on his body.

173
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:02,980
The police covered up that incident, after just one day.

174
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:05,860
And I could not do anything, back then.

175
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:09,160
I could not, I had no power.

176
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:13,360
But things are very different now.

177
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:20,490
I will get rid of Sinyeong Philharmonic by crushing its entire body, just like my son was killed.

178
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:24,140
Whatever is inside, I will dig everything out and make it all disappear.

179
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:31,430
Is that enough of an answer?

180
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:38,160
As I promised you, I will give you the stage that you want, Eun Ju.

181
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:44,040
In return, I hope that you will tell me

182
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:46,760
everything that you know.

183
00:14:55,760 --> 00:15:01,140
So Yi Yeong packed up all her things and returned to her home?

184
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:05,560
Yes, I tried to hold her down, but she insisted.

185
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:09,510
Alright, I will talk to her and convince her to come back to our home.

186
00:15:09,510 --> 00:15:12,380
Don't worry too much, Mom.

187
00:15:12,380 --> 00:15:14,750
Please do that.

188
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:21,190
Let me hang up. I think a customer came in.

189
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:25,310
Welcome.

190
00:15:25,310 --> 00:15:27,250
Yes, hello.

191
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:30,570
We are from the police station.

192
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:35,300
Do you know this man, Yun Yeong Gil?

193
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:41,110
We asked around, and heard that he recently worked at this shop.

194
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:44,960
To be honest, his dead body was discovered early this morning.

195
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:49,110
So we wanted to know since when and for how long he worked here.

196
00:15:56,980 --> 00:16:02,140
♫ Say you do ♫

197
00:16:02,860 --> 00:16:05,110
Excuse me?

198
00:16:05,110 --> 00:16:07,220
Welcome.

199
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:10,950
I'm sorry, but may I ask you a question?

200
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:12,780
Me?

201
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:15,090
- Yes.
- Well, alright.

202
00:16:15,090 --> 00:16:15,930
Perhaps...

203
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:20,200
Hello, we are from the police station.

204
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:22,080
♫ For wild is the wind ♫

205
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,550
This person has come here before?

206
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:25,460
Yes.

207
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:28,240
We found a receipt for this place among his personal things.

208
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:31,530
Yes, he was a regular here.

209
00:16:31,530 --> 00:16:34,620
This person was discovered dead early this morning.

210
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:35,610
What?

211
00:16:35,610 --> 00:16:38,510
When was the last time he was here?

212
00:16:38,510 --> 00:16:39,890
Yesterday.

213
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:42,430
Around 6:30 p.m.

214
00:16:42,430 --> 00:16:45,400
Was there anything different about him compared to the other times he was here?

215
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,450
He had flowers with him.

216
00:16:48,450 --> 00:16:52,860
I asked him if he was going to confess his feelings, and he smiled and replied, "it's something like that."

217
00:16:52,860 --> 00:16:53,940
What kind of flowers?

218
00:16:53,940 --> 00:16:59,150
It wasn't a particularly unusual bouquet. A few yellow roses?

219
00:16:59,150 --> 00:17:00,500
Was he alone?

220
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:03,190
Yes, he was always alone and yesterday, too.

221
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:08,540
Did he ever meet other people here, by any chance?

222
00:17:09,350 --> 00:17:11,950
I'm not sure.

223
00:17:11,950 --> 00:17:15,180
Hmm, well...

224
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:19,080
Thinking about it...

225
00:17:24,810 --> 00:17:27,000
He had flowers with him.

226
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,810
It wasn't a particularly unusual bouquet.

227
00:17:29,810 --> 00:17:32,850
A few yellow roses?

228
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:45,140
Where did he go?

229
00:19:05,740 --> 00:19:07,660
Did you do it?

230
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:10,580
Just what have you done?

231
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,830
What do you mean?

232
00:19:13,830 --> 00:19:17,910
Yun Yeong Gil didn't just slip and fall, did he? You did that, didn't you?

233
00:19:17,910 --> 00:19:22,470
Why are you suspecting me? Wasn't it you?

234
00:19:22,470 --> 00:19:24,600
What?

235
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:27,710
Have you gone nuts? Why would I kill him?

236
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:30,500
And why would I kill Yun Yeong Gil?

237
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:34,840
Wasn't Yun Yeong Gil one of your men?

238
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:39,540
Not just one, but two people. Aren't you too much?

239
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:43,570
Not just one, but two?

240
00:19:43,570 --> 00:19:45,300
I am dismayed.

241
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:47,240
So are you saying I killed two people?

242
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:49,830
Am I some murdering fiend who goes around killing people?

243
00:19:49,830 --> 00:19:52,800
I have a wife and kids. My youngest daughter is in 9th grade.

244
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:56,960
How dare you say such things?

245
00:19:56,960 --> 00:20:01,130
Professor, please stop making excuses.

246
00:20:01,130 --> 00:20:04,280
Someone who did this once, couldn't they do it again?

247
00:20:08,570 --> 00:20:11,820
Are you talking about Kim Ian again?

248
00:20:11,820 --> 00:20:16,330
You've been suspecting me for a year. But do you have evidence that I killed Kim ian?

249
00:20:16,330 --> 00:20:18,260
If you do, let's see it. Say it after you show it.

250
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:21,910
Isn't that what Yun Yeong Gil had, evidence of who killed Kim Ian?

251
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:28,140
So I killed Yun Yeong Gil in order to hide that evidence?

252
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:32,560
Don't accuse just anyone. Did you see me kill Yun Yeong Gil?

253
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:36,960
Did you see me kill Kim Ian? You saw nothing.

254
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:39,740
I regret not seeing it.

255
00:20:42,320 --> 00:20:44,460
Let me ask you one thing.

256
00:20:44,460 --> 00:20:49,370
Why did you pick me, back then?

257
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,510
What are you saying now?

258
00:20:51,510 --> 00:20:56,190
When you used school funds to send me to study abroad. You had many other pupils.

259
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:59,030
But why did you pick me?

260
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:02,900
Are you resenting me right now?

261
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:05,240
It wouldn't be enough if you bowed down to thank me.

262
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:09,260
Fine, I picked you because in you, I thought I saw myself when I was young.

263
00:21:09,260 --> 00:21:11,380
Why? Is that enough?

264
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:17,020
Conductor Nam Ju Wan, this is not a time for us to be doing this.

265
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:18,540
This isn't the time for us to fight.

266
00:21:18,540 --> 00:21:22,140
I am the person who put you in the position you are.

267
00:21:22,140 --> 00:21:23,300
You have a lot now.

268
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:27,630
I have a lot, too, much more than you. Do you want all this to collapse?

269
00:21:27,630 --> 00:21:29,260
No, right?

270
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:32,220
So please don't come to see me like this.

271
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:35,640
If the Chairwoman hears anything, it's all over for me.

272
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:38,430
I am about to go crazy.

273
00:22:03,620 --> 00:22:07,360
Be Careful of Glass

274
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,360
Oh, you shocked me.

275
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:16,350
What's with you? Do you have some business with me?

276
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:23,600
How did you come here? Did you follow me?

277
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:28,870
None of your business. You were having quite a conversation with Conductor.

278
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:30,120
So you eavesdropped?

279
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,740
I didn't mean to hear it, but I heard it.

280
00:22:32,740 --> 00:22:38,840
Two people were killed, and you are both accusing each other.

281
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:41,880
You are both pretty terrible.

282
00:22:43,150 --> 00:22:46,520
Did you come here to threaten me?

283
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:48,360
Out of my way.

284
00:22:49,490 --> 00:22:51,360
My younger brother died a year ago.

285
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:53,740
He was stabbed with a knife then run over by a car.

286
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:56,440
Who is your younger brother?

287
00:22:57,650 --> 00:23:00,810
Kim Ian?

288
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:03,010
Why ask me about him?

289
00:23:03,010 --> 00:23:05,030
What do I have to do with his death?

290
00:23:05,030 --> 00:23:08,770
Nam Ju Wan just said that you killed him.

291
00:23:08,770 --> 00:23:12,160
If your prized pupil says such a thing to you, there must be some reason, isn't there?

292
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,890
What reason can there be?

293
00:23:13,890 --> 00:23:18,380
Nam Ju Wan is just babbling nonsense, and you actually believe it?

294
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,910
I really did not kill anyone.

295
00:23:20,910 --> 00:23:24,350
Your brother or Yun Yeong Gil, I did not kill them.

296
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:26,960
If you cannot believe me, please investigate me.

297
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:30,360
Let's open it all up. I'm confident.

298
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,950
Is that enough?

299
00:23:34,970 --> 00:23:41,020
The conversation between you two, I recorded all of it, right here.

300
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:48,460
How and when I will use this, I will think it over slowly.

301
00:24:04,620 --> 00:24:06,790
Excuse me.

302
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,990
What brings you here so late?

303
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:19,650
The Conductor asked me to bring him something.

304
00:24:19,650 --> 00:24:21,360
Is that so?

305
00:24:22,280 --> 00:24:24,320
Work hard.

306
00:24:44,430 --> 00:24:46,870
Where did he go?

307
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,570
Don't come near me.

308
00:25:36,570 --> 00:25:38,840
Don't come near me, don't come near me!

309
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:40,070
Go away!

310
00:25:40,070 --> 00:25:42,190
Hong Yi Yeong!

311
00:25:46,460 --> 00:25:48,620
What are you doing there?

312
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,250
Who are you?

313
00:26:17,250 --> 00:26:18,470
Don't come near me.

314
00:26:18,470 --> 00:26:22,340
Don't come near me, don't come near me, don't come near me!

315
00:26:24,810 --> 00:26:28,510
Go away! Don't come near me, don't come near me!

316
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:42,790
Sunbae Ju Wan?

317
00:26:52,770 --> 00:26:55,650
You are Jang Do Hun, aren't you?

318
00:26:55,650 --> 00:26:57,740
Yes, I am.

319
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:02,160
We are from the police station.

320
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:22,570
Conductor, one year ago, in that warehouse, you were there with me, weren't you?

321
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:37,300
That knife, is that yours?

322
